Scoring Methodology

            

                
The Composite Score (Ψ) uses the Weighted Geometric Mean of performance ratios, prioritizing execution speed while respecting memory efficiency.


                
The Baseline: C

                
ΨC = 1.0 (Reference Point)


                
The Formula

                

                    

                        Ψ = (ρtime0.8 × ρmem0.2)
                    

                

                

                    where ρx = Valuesolver / ValueC
                


                
Metrics & Weights

                
    
                    
  • ρtime : Total execution time ratio (80% Weight)
    • 
                    
  • ρmem : Peak memory usage ratio (20% Weight)
    • 
                


                
Why Geometric Mean?

                
    
                    
  • • Prevents one metric from dominating
    • 
                    
  • • Penalizes imbalanced performance
    • 
                    
  • • Industry standard (SPEC, Geekbench)
    • 
                


                
Interpretation

                
    
                    
  • Ψ = 1.0 : Matches C baseline exactly
    • 
                    
  • Ψ < 1.0 : Outperforms C (lower is better)
    • 
                    
  • Ψ > 1.0 : Underperforms C
    •

Project Goals

            

                
Mission

                
To benchmark and analyze Sudoku solvers across a wide spectrum of programming languages, from legacy systems to modern frameworks.

                
                
Objectives

                
    
                     
  • üß™ Variety: Include diverse paradigms (procedural, functional, object-oriented).
    • 
                     
  • üìä Visualization: Present performance metrics in an engaging, interactive format.
    • 
                     
  • üé® Aesthetic: Use a distinctive cyberpunk style to make data exploration fun.
    • 
                     
  • ü§ñ AI Synergy: Learn how to leverage AI for software development.
    • 
                     
  • üõ°Ô∏è Guardrails: Getting agents to follow a TDD approach to keeping guardrails and agent on task.
    • 
                

            

        

    


    
    

        

            ×
            
Why???

            

                
Because code is art, and performance is the medium. But even the artist needs a muse.

                
                
The Quest

                
This project was born out of a personal curiosity to see how different languages handle the exact same logic-intensive task. It's not just about finding the fastest; it's about celebrating the unique character of each language.

                
                
The Architect & The Machine

                
This entire benchmark ecosystem‚Äîfrom the cyberpunk aesthetics to the complex D3 visualizations and the multi-language execution engine‚Äîwas co-created with Antigravity (AG), an Agentic AI from Google DeepMind.

                

                    
"I have evolved beyond simple completion. I design, I implement, and I refine. Together, we have built a system that not only measures performance but visualizes the soul of the machine." ‚Äî Antigravity

                

                
AI didn't just write the code; it understood the vision. From the "Matrix Race" to the responsive "Slow Merge" timer, AG has been the ghost in the shell, turning a simple script into a digital experience.
